    "However, this runs into issues to do with double-counting interactions.To illustrate this, we consider the simpler example of modelling the hole-doping regime of a (non-moiré) semiconductor whose single valence band maximum has kinetic energy E(p) = -p 2 2m *, where m * is the effective mass.",
    "We consider the conduction band to be sufficiently far separated in energy so that it is never occupied.",
    "If c † (p) is the electron creation operator for a valence state, then it is tempting to normal-order the interacting Hamiltonian asĤ?",
    "= - ′ p p 2 2m * c † (p)c(p) + 1 2A ′ p,p ′,q V (q)c † (p + q)c † (p ′ -q)c(p ′)c(p),(19)where the primes indicate that the summations are restricted so that the arguments of all fermion operators lie within the circular cutoff Λ, and we have ignored any nontrivial Bloch structure/form factors.",
    "A is the total area of the system."
